      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>green beans</strong> to a pot, cover them with <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook for 3-4 min or until tender</p><p>Meanwhile, drain and rinse your <strong>green lentils</strong></p><p>Once the beans are cooked, drain and run under <strong>cold water</strong> until cooled slightly</p><p>Add the <strong>drained</strong> <strong>green</strong> <strong>lentils </strong>and<strong> cooked beans</strong> to a large bowl</p>",
